 <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>...a series informed by ideas around \xe2\x80\x98big history\xe2\x80\x99, David Christian\xe2\x80\x99s notion that we should look for common themes and patterns .....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=Mankind%3A+The+Story+of+All+of+Us&amp;rft.date=2012-11-14&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BBC+History+Magazine&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.historyextra.com%2Ftv-and-radio%2Fmankind-story-all-us&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2Miuiui-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Miuiui_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Miuiui_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Stephen Pritchard (3 November 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2012/nov/04/for-the-record">"For the record"</a>. <i>The Observer</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>Prof Christian ... left for San Diego in 2001 but returned to Macquarie in 2009.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=For+the+record&amp;rft.au=Stephen+Pritchard&amp;rft.date=2012-11-03&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Observer&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftheobserver%2F2012%2Fnov%2F04%2Ffor-the-record&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2Mkjkjk-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mkjkjk_9-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mq.edu.au/about_us/faculties_and_departments/faculty_of_arts/mhpir/modern_history/staff/professor_david_christian/">"Professor David Christian"</a>. <i>Macquarie University</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=Professor+David+Christian&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Macquarie+University&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mq.edu.au%2Fabout_us%2Ffaculties_and_departments%2Ffaculty_of_arts%2Fmhpir%2Fmodern_history%2Fstaff%2Fprofessor_david_christian%2F&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Teaching Company, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.thegreatcourses.com/professors/david-christian/">David Christian</a> Great Courses professor reference page, Retrieved Sept. 8, 2014</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2Mksksk-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mksksk_11-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/1989/02/12/opinion/l-communism-knew-diversity-before-gorbachev-russian-peasant-s-diet-602689.html">"Communism Knew Diversity Before Gorbachev..."</a>. <i>The New York Times</i>. February 12, 1989<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>...As R.E.F. Smith and David Christian showed in 1984, in <i>Bread and Salt,</i> even dairy products were generally used as seasoning.....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=Communism+Knew+Diversity+Before+Gorbachev...&amp;rft.date=1989-02-12&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1989%2F02%2F12%2Fopinion%2Fl-communism-knew-diversity-before-gorbachev-russian-peasant-s-diet-602689.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2M27afsf-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tws2M27afsf_12-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/speakers/david_christian.html">"Speakers David Christian: Historian"</a>. <i>TED</i>. 2012-12-30. <q>...David Christian is by training a historian of Russia and the Soviet Union, but since the 1980s he has become interested in world history on very large scales.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=Speakers+David+Christian%3A+Historian&amp;rft.date=2012-12-30&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=TED&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ted.com%2Fspeakers%2Fdavid_christian.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-ttcweb-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ttcweb_13-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.thegreatcourses.com/tgc/courses/course_detail.aspx?cid=8050">"Big History: The Big Bang, Life on Earth, and the Rise of Humanity"</a>. The Teaching Company\'s Great Courses<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">15 May</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.btitle=Big+History%3A+The+Big+Bang%2C+Life+on+Earth%2C+and+the+Rise+of+Humanity&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=The+Teaching+Company%27s+Great+Courses&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thegreatcourses.com%2Ftgc%2Fcourses%2Fcourse_detail.aspx%3Fcid%3D8050&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2Mwrwrw-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mwrwrw_14-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mwrwrw_14-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-tws2Mwrwrw_14-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">David Christian (December 2010). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.historyandtheory.org/archives/indx4650.html">"The Return of Universal History"</a>. <i>History and Theory</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>49, 6-27 ...Today, however, there are many signs of a return to universal history....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=The+Return+of+Universal+History&amp;rft.au=David+Christian&amp;rft.date=2010-12&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=History+and+Theory&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.historyandtheory.org%2Farchives%2Findx4650.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">PD Smith (6 May 2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2005/may/07/featuresreviews.guardianreview25">"Time and headspace"</a>. <i>The Guardian</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>...Christian has written a history of Wellsian scale, travelling from the physics of the Big Bang to our current nuclear age....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=Time+and+headspace&amp;rft.au=PD+Smith&amp;rft.date=2005-05-06&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2005%2Fmay%2F07%2Ffeaturesreviews.guardianreview25&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-tws2Msdfsd-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tws2Msdfsd_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Roger Munting and Stephen Rashid (4 July 2010). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/2010/jul/05/ref-smith-obituary">"REF Smith obituary"</a>. <i>The Guardian</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-12-31</span></span>. <q>...His last monograph ... jointly written with David Christian....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADavid+Christian+%28historian%29&amp;rft.atitle=REF+Smith+obituary&amp;rft.au=Roger+Munting+and+Stephen+Rashid&amp;rft.date=2010-07-04&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftheguardian%2F2010%2Fjul%2F05%2Fref-smith-obituary&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="External_links">External links</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=David_Christian_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n96-115443">Works by or about David Christian</a> in libraries (<a href="/wiki/WorldCat" title="WorldCat">WorldCat</a> catalog)</li>\n<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ted.com/speakers/david_christian">David Christian</a> at <a href="/wiki/TED_(conference)" title="TED (conference)">TED</a> <a href="https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q1909499#P2611" title="Edit this at Wikidata"><img alt="Edit this at Wikidata" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/10px-Blue_pencil.svg.png" width="10" height="10" style="vertical-align: text-top" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/15px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/20px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="600" /></a>\n<ul>\n<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/david_christian_big_history">TED Talk: David Christian: The history of our world in 18 minutes (TED2011)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.teach12.com/ttcx/CourseDescLong2.aspx?cid=8050">Big History: The Big Bang, Life on Earth, and the Rise of Humanity</a> The Teaching Company course taught by David Christian</li>\n</ul>\n<div role="navigation" class="navbox" aria-labelledby="Big_History" style="padding:3px">\n<table class="nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner" style="border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit">\n<tr>\n<th scope="col" class="navbox-title" colspan="2" style="text-align:center;">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Big_History" title="Template:Big History"><abbr title="View this template" style="text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">v</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Big_History" title="Template talk:Big History"><abbr title="Discuss this template" style="text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">t</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Big_History&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template" style="text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="Big_History" style="font-size:114%;margin:0 4em"><a href="/wiki/Big_History" title="Big History">Big History</a></div>\n</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" class="navbox-group" style="text-align:center;;width:1%;background: #F5F5DC">Themes and subjects</th>\n<td class="navbox-list navbox-odd" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px">\n<div style="padding:0em 0.25em">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Chronology_of_the_universe" title="Chronology of the universe">Chronology of the universe</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Physical_cosmology" title="Physical cosmology">Cosmic evolution</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Deep_time" title="Deep time">Deep time</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Geologic_time_scale" title="Geologic time scale">Time scales</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Goldilocks_principle" title="Goldilocks principle">Goldilocks principle</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Modernity" title="Modernity">Modernity</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" class="navbox-group" style="text-align:center;;width:1%;background: #F5F5DC">Eight thresholds</th>\n<td class="navbox-list navbox-even" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px">\n<div style="padding:0em 0.25em">\n<ul>\n<li>1: <b>Creation</b> - <a href="/wiki/Big_Bang" title="Big Bang">Big Bang</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cosmogony" title="Cosmogony">cosmogony</a></li>\n<li>2: <b>Stars</b> - <a href="/wiki/Star" title="Star">creation of stars</a></li>\n<li>3: <b>Elements</b> - <a href="/wiki/Chemical_element" title="Chemical element">creation of chemical elements</a> inside <a href="/wiki/Stellar_evolution" title="Stellar evolution">dying stars</a></li>\n<li>4: <b>Planets</b> - <a href="/wiki/Planet" title="Planet">formation of planets</a></li>\n<li>5: <b>Life</b> - <a href="/wiki/Abiogenesis" title="Abiogenesis">abiogenesis</a> and <a href="/wiki/Evolution" title="Evolution">evolution</a> of <a href="/wiki/Life" title="Life">life</a></li>\n<li>6: <b>Humans</b> - development of <i><a href="/wiki/Homo_sapiens" title="Homo sapiens">Homo sapiens</a></i>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Paleolithic" title="Paleolithic">Paleolithic era</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>7: <b>Agriculture</b> - <a href="/wiki/Neolithic_Revolution" title="Neolithic Revolution">Agricultural Revolution</a></li>\n<li>8: <b>Modernity</b> - <a href="/wiki/Modern_history" title="Modern history">modern era</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" class="navbox-group" style="text-align:center;;width:1%;background: #F5F5DC">Web-based education</th>\n<td class="navbox-list navbox-odd" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px">\n<div style="padding:0em 0.25em">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Big_History_Project" title="Big History Project">Big History Project</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Crash_Course_(YouTube)" title="Crash Course (YouTube)"><i>Crash Course Big History</i></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/ChronoZoom" title="ChronoZoom">ChronoZoom</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" class="navbox-group" style="text-align:center;;width:1%;background: #F5F5DC">Notable people</th>\n<td class="navbox-list navbox-even" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px">\n<div style="padding:0em 0.25em">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Walter_Alvarez" title="Walter Alvarez">Walter Alvarez</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Eric_Chaisson" title="Eric Chaisson">Eric Chaisson</a></li>\n<li><a class="mw-selflink selflink">David Christian</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Bill_Gates" title="Bill Gates">Bill Gates</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Carl_Sagan" title="Carl Sagan">Carl Sagan</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Graeme_Snooks" title="Graeme Snooks">Graeme Snooks</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Cynthia_Stokes_Brown" title="Cynthia Stokes Brown">Cynthia Stokes Brown</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div role="navigation" class="navbox" aria-label="Navbox" style="padding:3px">\n<table class="nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner" style="border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit">\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" class="navbox-group" style="width:1%"><a href="/wiki/Help:Authority_control" title="Help:Authority control">Authority control</a></th>\n<td class="navbox-list navbox-odd" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px">\n<div style="padding:0em 0.25em">\n<ul>\n<li><span class="nowrap"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/identities/containsVIAFID/116002843">WorldCat Identities</a></span></li>\n<li><span class="nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Virtual_International_Authority_File" title="Virtual International Authority File">VIAF</a>: <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://viaf.org/viaf/116002843">116002843</a></span></span></li>\n<li><span class="nowrap"><a href="/wiki/International_St